article.headline: Oral Roberts 81, IUPUI 71
article.story: INDIANAPOLIS -- Warren Niles scored 23 points and Oral Roberts won its ninth game in a row, defeating IUPUI 81-71 Saturday night. Michael Craion had 18 points and 10 rebounds for the Golden Eagles (16-4, 8-0 Summit), and Damen Bell-Holter had 18 points and nine boards. Dominique Morrison had 12 points for Oral Roberts. Niles made 10 of 11 free throws, while IUPUI as a team was 8 for 12 from the foul line. Alex Young led all scorers with 27 points for the Jaguars (8-12, 2-6), but Ian Chiles was their only other player in double figures with 10 points. It was IUPUI's fourth straight loss, following a six-game winning streak.
